DTO - data transfer object

used to tranfer daata btwn API layer (cobtrikker) and service/entity layer 
with out exposing the ful domain model entity

why DTO

prevents tight coupling with database
  expsoing entities, any database change might breat the api contract
encapsulation of data(hide internal structure
  entity class usually map directly to the db tables
  
validation and transformation
    dto help to validate requests - @NotNull, @Size , @Email
improved API security- direclty expsong entity might leaks sensitive DB fiels or relationshps

MODELMAPPER LIBRARY:

sipliefie the conversion btwn different java objects
helps in removing repetive code to copy fiels manually
used in springboot to convert btwn DTO's and entites for clearner, maintainable code

DTO TO ENTITY (WHEN RECEIVING API REQUEST)
ENTITY TO DTO (WHEN SENDING API RESPONSE)



